block content

  +state('North Carolina', '/assets/images/flag-north-carolina.svg', 'The Tar Heel State', 'November 21, 1789', 'border')

  .intro
    p The first official flag of North Carolina was adopted a month after the state seceded from the union in 1861. The design of the flag is credited to Raleigh artist, William G. Browne.
    p The flag has had two other versions since, with a redesign introduced in 1885 by then state Adjutant General, Johnston Jones.
    p The current version of the flag was adopted in 1991.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The North Carolina state flag features a blue union the full width of the flag and one-third the length. The remaining area features two equally-proportioned horizontal bars of red and white.
      p Within the blue union is a white five-pointed star with the letters ‘N’ and ‘C’ in gold on either side. They are encircled by two scrolls inscribed with two dates: “May 20th, 1775” above and “April 12th, 1776” below.
    .visual.flag
      img.border(src='/assets/images/flag-north-carolina.svg')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-north-carolina-icon-star.svg')
          h4 Star, N, & C
          p The star remains from the first design of the North Carolina flag. The letters ‘N’ and ‘C’ were added in 1885 and stand for North Carolina.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-north-carolina-icon-may-20.svg')
          h4 May 20th 1775
          p May 20th is the date of the alleged #[a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mecklenburg_Declaration_of_Independence') Mecklenburg Declaration of Independence] which is disputed by historians. On this date, the citizens of Mecklenburg County supposedly declared themselves free.
          p Historians do agree that on May 31st, 1775 Mecklenburg County adopted the Mecklenburg Resolves, a set of anti-British resolutions, more than a year before the U.S. Declaration would be signed.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-north-carolina-icon-april-12.svg')
          h4 April 12th 1776
          p April 12th is the date that North Carolina authorized its delegates to vote for declaring independence to the Continental Congress. Resolutions were written and they became known as the #[a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halifax_Resolves') Halifax Resolves].

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p Colors include blue, red, white, and gold. The blue and red match the United States flag.
