  .guide
    .content
      h2 Production
      p The flag’s length should be half more than its width (a proportion of 2:3). So if the flag has a hoist of 4 feet, its fly should be 6 feet.
      p If resized, it must maintain these proportions.
    .visual
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-north-carolina-dimensions.svg')

  .guide.wide.timeline
    .content
      h2 Previous iterations
      ul.visual.flag-list
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img.border(src='/assets/images/flag-north-carolina-1861-1865.svg')
          h4 1861-1865
          p Designed by William G. Browne. “May 20th 1861” is the date North Carolina seceded to join the Confederacy.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img.border(src='/assets/images/flag-north-carolina-1885-1991.svg')
          h4 1885–1991
          p Blue and red stripes are swapped and the letters ‘N’ and ‘C’ are added. “May 20th 1861” is replaced with “April 12th 1776” and both dates get golden scrolls underneath.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag(style='margin-bottom:8.274%'): img.border(src='/assets/images/flag-north-carolina.svg')
          h4 1991-Present
          p The current flag of North Carolina. It is widened to a 2:3 proportion instead of 3:4.
        li.flag-item

